The vet assistants are thoughtful, kind, and really good at what they do.
I am a bit of a crazy cat lady, and they never make me feel bad about my (over) concern for my cats.

We took our black lab pup to Northside a week ago for his first visit after coming home.
They were very prompt at answering the phone, and took the time to find an appointment slot that fit our schedule.
On the day before our scheduled visit, they gave us a courtesy call to ensure that everything was still good to go for the impending visit.
The day of the visit, every staff member that was near the entryway introduced themselves to both my fianc√© and myself...AND made a point to play with our pup to make everyone feel welcome.
The scheduled appointment began on-time and we met with Debbie (very nice and informative vet tech).
From Debbie, we segwayed into meeting Dr. Brooks.
Again - very friendly and had a wonderful demeanor with all of us.
After all the checkup, medicine, and vaccines were administered they set up our next appointment in the exam room and were able to take payment there, too.
Two days following our appointment, we received a thank you note for choosing NAH.
Pretty neat that they took the time to do that!
Overall I found our experience with NAH to be excellent, and I will openly suggest to my fellow pet-owners to check them out!

